<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 28 at 7:48PM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of northwestern Oldham,
western Dallam and Hartley Counties through 845 PM CDT...
At 748 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 10 miles west of Ware to 8 miles east of
Romero. Movement was northeast at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Dalhart, Hartley, Texline, Channing, Ware and Romero.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
